---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MarketStructureLine from '../components/MarketStructureLine.astro';

const lastUpdated = "June 17, 2026";
---

<Layout title="Now" description="What I'm currently focused on.">
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-serif mb-4">Now</h1>
      <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs font-sans lowercase tracking-widest">
        last updated: {lastUpdated}
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose text-text-secondary">
      <p>
        This is a "now" page, inspired by <a href="https://sivers.org/nowff" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent-bright hover:underline">Derek Sivers</a>. It's a snapshot of my current focus.
      </p>

      <h2>Trading</h2>
      <p>
        I am currently refining my execution on the 15-minute timeframe, focusing specifically on high-probability reversals at key supply and demand zones. I'm working on reducing my trade frequency and increasing my strike rate.
      </p>

      <h2>Building</h2>
      <p>
        This site is my current focus. I'm building "Garden" as a place to think in public and hold myself accountable to my learning goals. I'm also exploring automated backtesting tools using Python and some proprietary data sets.
      </p>

      <h2>Learning</h2>
      <p>
        Deep-diving into market auction theory and psychological resilience. Reading <em>The Daily Stoic</em> by Ryan Holiday to help maintain emotional neutrality during volatile sessions.
      </p>

      <MarketStructureLine variant="divider" class="h-4 w-full my-12 opacity-30" />
      
      <p class="text-sm italic">
        Currently based in a quiet corner of the internet, building for the long term.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
